description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity is available for a Cancer Pathway Support Co-ordinator at University Hospitals Birmingham within a busy Cancer Services department. Working across all hospital sites of the organisation the post holder will be responsible for the centralised management of tertiary referrals, high priority radiology/histopathology alerts and cancer data collection.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be required to facilitate communications with both external organisations and internal stakeholders to ensure a frictionless transfer of care for patients on a cancer pathway. Be able to effectively manage, organise a conflicting workload with time sensitive deadlines and maintain a high standard of accuracy and attention to detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is on a Fixed term basis for 12 months, due to funding.&lt;/p&gt;
